    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A non-continuous lace named for a town in East Devon, where it is thought to have originated from around the 18th century. Inspired by Brussels lace, typical motifs are roses, thistles and cloverleaves. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
